      • getMaxDepth

        public int getMaxDepth()
        The maximum depth for term extraction, where including a dependent's dependents gives a depth of 2. Some dependents are considered "zero-depth" and don't add to the depth - such as conjuncts or determinants.

      • getTermStopTags

        public Set<String> getTermStopTags()
        A dependent which, as soon as it is reached, causes the expansion to stop, e.g. relative pronouns or conjugated verbs. It is assumed that no noun phrase containing these should be considered a term.

      • setTermStopTags

        public void setTermStopTags(Set<String> termStopTags)

      • getNonTopLevelLabels

        public Set<String> getNonTopLevelLabels()
        Dependency labels which should never be included with a term governor - e.g. determinants or coordination. In other words, we accept the term "apple" but not "apple and orange" or "the apple".
